1.title: Making a Track in Reason
1.plot: Working on a new track in Propellerhead Reason: "Glory" Gear: Akai MPK61 - M-Audio 88 - Washburn N4 Nuno Bettencourt - David Laake Custom Studio Composer Desk I used Kong, Redrum, Subtractor, NNXT, a lot of compressors, mixers, and matrix units to vary the percussion elements.

2.title: Behind The Scenes Inside the Studio: - Ivory Cunanan
2.plot: Produced by VisionQuest Sound. Creating music and recording tracks in Propellerhead Reason. Recording bass, drums, guitars, vocals, keyboards, and rhythm tracks. Includes pre production footage and vocals recording. Gear used: Akai MPK 61, Roland TR8 rhythm performer, Washburn N4 Guitar, M-Audio Keystation 88, KRK Speakers.

3.title: How Great is Our God Cover with Danielle H & Philip
3.plot: Cover of Chris Tomlin's 'How Great is our God' Produced by VisionQuest Sound Philip Garcia. Featuring the artist Danielle H.

4.title: Sleep Walk Cover on ukulele with Philip & Kimberly Lee on vocals
4.plot: Just having fun with another Hawaiian theme and black and white effects. Here are some of the behind the scenes footage of the ukulele sessions with the artist Kimberly Lee. I played this song many times before, but it was a real joy to record with a singer (since this song was originally an instrumental song written by Santo and Johnny in 1959).

5.title: How to program the TR-8 In the Air Tonight Drum Beat by Phil Collins
5.plot: Just thought I'd share my insight on how to program the classic drum beat on Roland's TR-8. Originally done on the CR-78. Basically, it's a 2 Bar Drum pattern using the default 808 kit from the TR-8.

imdb.plot outline: Los Angeles based music talk show host Philip Garcia started his music career at age 8, learning music from his dad who is a music teacher. Known for his great ear, Philip has been producing and collaborating with musicians, bands, and Film/TV projects worldwide. His credits include NBC, Warner Bros, MTV, Fox, Miramax, and countless Grammy nominees. Philip is constantly pushing the musical boundaries of his favorite genres including world, jazz, pop, R&B, cinematic and gospel. He founded VisionQuest Sound in 2000 and has been interviewing and producing with celebrated musical talent all over the world.
